{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"LIVE DEPLOY (2026-07-02): epic code landed on main via Gerrit change 141 (MERGED + replicated to GitHub main) — dogfooded the existing LLM-Review gate, incl. remediating a real bot BLOCK (wired g2p materialize + hooks-enable into compose-up.sh). Deployed to the prod box: extended Gerrit image (python3.11 + g2p 0.3.1) built + running, hooks plugin enabled, g2p config materialized from SSM, project.config (Verified label + ACL + INACTIVE submit-req) pushed to refs/meta/config, replication.config broadened to refs/changes/*. Provisioned: SSM secrets (g2p-github-pat, ci-gerrit-ssh-key), GitHub repo vars + GERRIT_SSH_PRIVKEY secret, and the rebar-ci-bot Gerrit service account (SSH-auth verified).\n\nE2E BLOCKED by an external g2p bug: on patchset-created the g2p hook fires but crashes in gerrit_to_platform/helpers.py:191 get_change_id — its regex '.*~.*~(I.*)' expects project~branch~I<hash>, but Gerrit 3.14.1 passes change='rebar~142' (project~number) -> IndexError -> no workflow_dispatch -> no Verified vote. So CI does not yet dispatch.\n\nGate deliberately NOT activated (Verified submit-req stays applicableIf=is:false) — activating with a broken voter would block all submits. LLM-Review gate unaffected/working. NEXT: fix the g2p change-id incompatibility (upgrade/patch g2p or adjust the Gerrit hook change-id format), re-run E2E, THEN activate. Infra + PR #116 otherwise complete."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782972214411673001,"uuid":"e62f3b88-4687-4776-9c3a-e288d472d060"}